The doomsday task was both challenging and rewarding. Despite beginning the task behind (i joined the course in week 4) and missing the explanatory lectures, i quickly grapsed the general nature of the task and the concept of a doomsday function.

I set out by attempting to understand what the doomsday method of finding a weekday given a certain date entailed. A wikipedia article titled "The Doomsday rule" proved to be highly useful. The process was broken down into 3 parts

1.Determine the "anchor day" for the century.

2.Use the anchor day for the century to calculate the doomsday for the year.

3.Choose the closest date out of the ones that always fall on the doomsday (e.g. 4/4, 6/6, 8/8), and count the number of days (modulo 7) between that date and the date in question to arrive at the day of the week.

